What's a neobank? The future of digital banking explained
Product · Financial basics
 · 
15 December 2025
Clément Bolmont
The way we manage our money has changed dramatically in the last decade. Gone are the days when visiting a branch was the only way to open an account or solve a problem. Today, a new generation of financial providers has emerged, offering their services entirely through powerful, intuitive mobile apps. This modern approach to money management is what we call neobanking, and it's reshaping the financial landscape across the UK and the world.

A neobank is a financial technology (fintech) company that offers banking-like services exclusively through a digital platform, typically a mobile app. Unlike traditional banks, neobanks operate without any physical branches, which allows them to focus entirely on customer experience, low costs, and innovative features.

They aim to simplify your financial life, offering features like real-time budgeting, instant transfers, and international spending capabilities, all controlled from your smartphone. The key to understanding neobanks, however, lies in their licensing status, which we explain in detail below.

